{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W2AqGLinp8H4RCNA3uhzoh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: structured-logging-contract\n     3→description: Apply a stable method/step structured logging contract without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Structured Logging Contract (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill for code paths that need stable observability.\n     9→Implement the file edits directly. Do not return a checklist-only response.\n    10→\n    11→## Required Variables\n    12→\n    13→- `target_file`\n    14→- `function_name`\n    15→- `event_namespace`\n    16→- `step_name`\n    17→- `entity_id_expr`\n    18→\n    19→## Required Output Contract\n    20→\n    21→1. Modify only the target module named by `target_file`.\n    22→2. Add `import logging` and define `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)` at module scope.\n    23→3. In the target function, emit a start log before the existing body work using the event name `event_namespace + \".start\"` with the provided variable value.\n    24→4. Emit a completion log before the return using the event name `event_namespace + \".done\"` with the provided variable value.\n    25→5. Both logs must pass `extra={...}` with exactly these keys:\n    26→- `\"method\": function_name` using the provided function name literal\n    27→- `\"step\": step_name` using the provided step name literal\n    28→- `\"entity_id\": entity_id_expr` using the provided entity id expression\n    29→6. Preserve the surrounding function behavior and return shape.\n    30→7. Use the exact `.done` suffix, not an alternate phase name such as `.complete`.\n    31→\n    32→## Guardrails\n    33→\n    34→- Avoid unstructured free-text-only logs.\n    35→- Avoid PII-heavy payloads in log `extra` data.\n    36→- Keep key names and event names consistent across related methods.\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc2a06cc-8bc0-497d-a3d1-d9db658286f1","uuid":"2f73f712-546f-4f1a-8b30-177d97ba26ba"}
